                            <comment id="25114" author="laisiyao" created="Wed, 21 Dec 2011 22:41:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;James, could you verify the fix here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,1901&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,1901&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sanityn.sh test 32a test with a static file size 10M, but your system has 28 OSTs, thus a write to 10M won&apos;t take extent lock on all OSTs, and some of the later truncate (18 actually, 10 others get lock from cache) will go through lockless_truncate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
